Cook noodles according to package direction; drain. Cook sausage, onion and garlic in large skillet until meat is done; drain. Stir in tomato paste, 2 cups water, oregano and basil. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, 20 minutes. Combine ricotta cheese, spinach, 1 cup mozzarella cheese, parmesan cheese, egg and salt. Spread about 1/2 cup cheese mixture over each noodle; roll up. Place seam side down in 13x9 inch baking dish. Pour sauce over rolls. Sprinkle with remaining mozzarella cheese. Cover and bake in preheated 350 degree F oven, 35 minutes or until cheese is melted.